# common — Shared resources

This folder contains the shared infrastructure for all projects managed with m_AI_l.
It is not a project — it is the backbone that all projects and threads rely on.

The location of this folder is determined by ARO during initial setup.

---

## Getting started

To set up a new project or invite a new thread, open a new Claude conversation and paste:

```
Execute [path to this folder]\skills\aro.md
```

Replace `[path to this folder]` with the actual path to your common folder (e.g. `C:\dev\common`).
ARO will detect your language and guide you through the rest.

---

## Structure

```
common\
├── README.md                        # This file
├── common_conventions.md            # Local conventions for this installation
├── projects_config.md               # Central registry of all active projects
├── projects_config_archive.md       # Archive of completed or abandoned projects
├── roster.md                        # Team roster for common threads
└── skills\
    ├── commun.md                    # m_AI_l discovery hub — read at session start
    ├── m_AI_l_help.md               # m_AI_l user manual (all triggers)
    ├── mailbox_read.md              # Read and archive messages  (MAIL!, MSG?)
    ├── mailbox_write.md             # Send messages  (SEND?, SEND!, SEND! HANDLE)
    ├── mailbox_init.md              # Initialization utility (called by onboarding)
    ├── onboarding.md                # Invite a new or existing thread
    ├── briefing.md                  # Self-integration for an existing thread
    ├── renew.md                     # Replace a saturating or crashed thread
    ├── add_project.md               # Register a new project
    └── aro.md                       # Onboarding agent for new users
```

---

## Local conventions

This installation has a set of local conventions (session modes, navigation rules, etc.)
documented in `common_conventions.md`. New threads load this file automatically at startup.

If you are setting up a new installation, you can adapt or replace `common_conventions.md`
to match your own conventions — it is not distributed and will not be overwritten by updates.

---

## Projects

Active projects and their paths are tracked in `projects_config.md`.
This is the single source of truth for project locations and status.
